  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nWhile empty SSZ vectors are illegal types, empty SSZ lists are valid, and can be encountered in the Beacon Chain spec. As currently implemented, empty SSZ lists are not merkleized at all.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Empty SSZ lists should be merkleized per the v0.8.+ SSZ spec, instead of being skipped. This will likely require multiple static functions to handle merkleizing List<UnsignedLong>, List<SimpleOffsetSerializable>, etc. instead of the more generic implementation as currently exists.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** Hash tree root of an empty list should return the merkle root according to the algorithm in the SSZ spec.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** Hash tree root of an empty list fails to return a merkle root at all, and instead returns an empty byte array (Bytes.EMPTY/byte[0]).\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\nSee https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/blob/v0.8.1/specs/simple-serialize.md#merkleization",
